| `/knowledge-review` | KnowledgeReviewLive | Knowledge expansion review |

## Testing

When writing tests, do not use external APIs. Use snapshots instead.
See `test/support/http_snapshot.ex` for more information.



### Running Tests

```bash
mix test                           # All tests (excludes slow, benchmark, gpu)
mix test --only benchmark          # Accuracy threshold tests
mix test --only integration        # Integration tests
mix test --exclude requires_lstm   # Skip LSTM-dependent tests
```

### Test Helpers

- `test/support/lstm_test_helpers.ex` - Model compatibility checking, test model generation
- Tests use real models with graceful degradation when models are incompatible
- `@moduletag :benchmark` for accuracy threshold tests (excluded by default)

## Code Style

### Elixir Conventions

- **No regex for text processing** - use `Tokenizer` functions
- **No `String.contains?` for NLP** - use trained classifiers
- GenServers for stateful processes
- ETS for fast concurrent lookups (Gazetteer, world context cache)
- Pattern matching over conditionals when possible
- `Task.async` for parallel work in the pipeline

### Phoenix/LiveView

- Use `<Layouts.app>` wrapper in templates
- Use `<.input>` and `<.form>` components
- WorldContext on_mount hook for persistent world selection
- PubSub topics: `brain:status`, `brain:learning`, `brain:conversations`, `training:progress`, `knowledge:review`, `learning:novel_input`, `training:requests`, `world_models:status`
- No inline `<script>` tags - use app.js hooks
- Tailwind CSS + daisyUI for styling

### ML Framework Stack

- `Nx` ~0.10 - Numerical computing
- `Axon` ~0.8 - Neural network framework
- `EXLA` ~0.10 - XLA compiler backend (GPU acceleration)
- `Scholar` ~0.3 - Statistical/ML functions
- Erlang `:erlang.binary_to_term` / `term_to_binary` for model serialization

## Autonomous Learning System

The system learns autonomously from conversations, research, and outcomes.
All autonomous features are opt-in and gated by safety mechanisms.

### Key Modules

| Module | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `ComprehensionAssessor` | 8-dimension self-interrogation gate for knowledge acquisition |
| `ComprehensionProfile` | Assessment result struct (verdict, gaps, learnable flag) |
| `DimensionEvaluators` | 8 evaluator functions reading from ChunkAnalysis fields |
| `IntentRegistry` (GenServer) | Runtime-updatable intent metadata (ETS + JSON persistence, compile-time fallback) |
| `IntentAutoPromoter` | Auto-approves intent variations (5/day cap) |
| `LearningTriggers` | Conversation novelty → auto-triggered research sessions (2/day cap) |
| `ReviewQueue` (auto-approval) | Auto-approves high-confidence corroborated findings (10/day cap) |
| `TrainingExampleBuffer` | Collects high-activation outcomes → incremental TF-IDF updates |
| `ConsolidationBridge` | Bridges SemanticFacts from memory consolidation to BeliefStore |
| `EntityPromoter` | Auto-promotes discovered entities to Gazetteer (>= 3 occurrences) |
| `BeliefStore` (decay) | Inferred belief confidence decay + JTMS node creation |

### PubSub Topics (Autonomous Learning)

| Topic | Events | Subscribers |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| `knowledge:review` | `:candidate_approved`, `:candidate_rejected`, `:candidate_added` | ComprehensionAssessor (weight evolution) |
| `learning:novel_input` | `{:novel_input, text, score, domain}` | LearningTriggers |
| `training:requests` | `{:retrain_requested, world_id, :drift_guard}` | TrainingServer |

### Config Kill Switches

- `auto_extraction_enabled` (epistemic config) — gates event→belief extraction
- `auto_approval_enabled` (application env) — gates ReviewQueue auto-approval
- `intent_promotion_enabled` (application env) — gates novelty detection → review queue

## Quick Reference

```bash
mix phx.server                     # Start dev server
iex -S mix phx.server              # Start with IEx

mix train --name "v1" --compare    # Train + track experiment
mix evaluate --save --compare      # Evaluate + save + compare

Brain.SystemStatus.get_all()       # Check all statuses
Brain.ML.LSTM.UnifiedModel.ready?()
Brain.ML.CorpusManager.corpus_size()
```

```elixir
# Test analysis pipeline
Brain.Analysis.Pipeline.process("Hello! What's the weather in NYC?")

# Test intent classification
Brain.ML.IntentClassifierSimple.classify("What's the weather?")

# Test LSTM sentiment
Brain.ML.LSTM.UnifiedModel.classify_sentiment("I love this!")

# Test slot detection
Brain.Analysis.SlotDetector.detect("weather.query", [])

# Test evaluation
Brain.ML.Evaluation.accuracy(predictions, actuals)

# Comprehension assessment
Brain.Analysis.ComprehensionAssessor.assess(chunk_analyses)
Brain.Analysis.ComprehensionAssessor.stats()
Brain.Analysis.ComprehensionAssessor.reset_weights()

# Runtime intent registration
Brain.Analysis.IntentRegistry.register_intent("my.new_intent", %{"domain" => "custom", "category" => "directive"})

# Learning triggers status
Brain.Knowledge.LearningTriggers.stats()

# Training example buffer status
Brain.ML.TrainingExampleBuffer.stats()
Brain.ML.TrainingExampleBuffer.flush()

# Entity promoter status
World.EntityPromoter.stats()
```
